metadata.name: Planetarium #1
metadata.description:
A generative planetarium built using ThreeJS.

Each token produces a unique planetarium solar system. 
The Number of planets is random, there will be at least 3, but up to 10.
Each planet is random in size, distance from sun, orbit speed, rotation, texture and orbit inclination.

There are 6 Sun textures, 6 different space backgrounds and 33 Planet textures so every Mint will produce a random set of planets of varying sizes, speeds and texture.

The background and sun are also random from a selection of 6 textures.

The solar system is interactive, rotation, pan and zoom.

Collect and own your own mini solar system. 

Textures are from: https://www.premiumbeat.com/blog/space-kit-free-space-elements/, https://www.solarsystemscope.com/textures/ and https://planet-texture-maps.fandom.com/wiki/Planet_Texture_Maps_Wiki

metadata.name: Scorpion Abstraction #34
metadata.description:
Scorpions perform a courtship ritual that resembles a dance, sometimes known as a promenade à deux (French for "walk for two"). The details vary by species, but if the female shows interest in the male, they typically begin by facing off and holding onto one another's pedipalps, then rotating back and forth together with their tails (technically metasoma) raised above their backs. They sometimes bump their metasoma together without stinging, according to the San Diego Zoo, in a behavior called "clubbing."3﻿

The dance may last anywhere from minutes to hours. At the end of the dance, the male deposits his spermatophore on the ground for the female, then leaves.

metadata.name: Meet Arty #151
metadata.description:
Future royalties are shared 50% with the original minters!

Who is Arty?

Arty is the name given to this symbol by the friendly folks of Newberry, South Carolina. The symbol itself can be seen carved into the architectural moulding of the Old Newberry Hotel (est. 1878). No one knows why, when or by whom the symbol was created but many of the artists of Newberry Made have adopted it as their maker’s mark. Learn more about us at www.NewberryMade.com. 

#NewberryIsAnArtTown

Why is there a Red Dot in the bottom corner?

The red dot is my signature for an ongoing series of generative art on fxhash (a shout-out to my first project). I will continue to utilize red dots as a design element in future work.

About the token

- The canvas is square and responsive based on your viewport
- Press “s” to save (image file type is SVG)
- Owners will be given priority access to future reserve lists
- Coded using p5js & SVGCanvas v2.0.3


About the Artist

Robert Matheson is a community engaged artist from Newberry, South Carolina. His work is focused on improving the health and well-being of others through the arts. In 2019 Robert established Newberry Made, a local artist & maker registry that has grown to over 190 members.

Robert's most recent creation is the NFT Museum of Newberry, SC. A creative space focused on providing NFT art education, collaboration and exhibition to help artists and the broader community benefit from emerging digital economies. Learn more at www.RobertMatheson.com and www.NonFungibleTokenMuseum.org
